  "market_context": "YM daily chart in a downtrend where Friday expanded lower into an objective, sweeping a prior swing low around 43000 that had created a previous high, setting up a potential new phase of price at the weekly level.",
  "key_observation": "Classic expansion weekly profile does not require a Tuesday low — Monday formed the low via a candle-2 closure with an hourly change in state of delivery, enabling Tuesday and Wednesday continuations higher.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified Friday's expansion lower into an objective, taking out the swing low that had created the prior high.",
    "Step 2: Noted no candle closure formed on Friday, so waited for the next candle (Monday) to print.",
    "Step 3: Observed Monday print an open-low and move higher, forming a wick on the weekly time frame and a candle-2 closure.",
    "Step 4: Dropped to the hourly time frame to confirm a change in the state of delivery — series of down-close candles that made the low were closed through.",
    "Step 5: With Monday forming the low, anticipated Tuesday continuation higher toward targets above.",
    "Step 6: Tuesday delivered a move higher and closed over Monday's high, validating continuation into Wednesday.",
    "Step 7: Wednesday expanded aggressively, taking out the highs above and completing the Monday-Tuesday-Wednesday expansion sequence.",
    "Step 8: Noted that after three days of expansion, price should be avoided due to risk of a new phase forming."
  ],
  "outcome": "Successful classic expansion profile — Monday low held, Tuesday closed above Monday high, Wednesday expanded and took out targeted highs.",
  "lessons": "A classic expansion weekly profile can form its low on Monday rather than Tuesday. Confirmation requires a weekly candle-2 closure paired with an hourly change in state of delivery, then anticipate Tuesday/Wednesday continuation but avoid entries after three days of expansion.",
